channel.title: [SOLVED] Cant log onto my own server using other computer? [508]
channel.description: i need some help. im hosting a server and theres like 15 people on. i want my bro to play on other computer, but when he tries to log on, it always says that error_jconnect5 or something. im using the same router if it helps. im also using milk 508 custom LD client with an IP Changer. What should i put in the ip? please help!

item.dc:creator: @Tree_Climber Tree_Climber
item.description:
@Tree_Climber wrote:

You Are Sick:

If it is on the same network you’ll need to fill in at ip as “Localhost” or “127.0.0.1”

No you would use the computers internal IP address which can be obtained by typing “ipconfig” in the DOS prompt on Windows.
